.TH SPACEGL_HUD 1 "2026-04-19" "SpaceGL @VERSION@" "SpaceGL Manual"
.SH NAME
spacegl_hud \- SpaceGL ncurses heads-up display
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spacegl_hud
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spacegl_hud
is an ncurses-based heads-up display for the SpaceGL engine.
It reads galaxy state from shared memory (SHM) and renders real-time
telemetry including ship position, energy levels, shield status,
cargo, and galaxy-wide entity counts directly in the terminal.
.PP
The HUD supports a paginated Shared Memory Inspector toggled with the
.B m
key, navigable with
.B n
(next page) and
.B p
(previous page). It also displays HMAC-SHA256 cryptographic telemetry
for galaxy data synchronization.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH KEYS
.TP
.B m
Toggle Shared Memory Inspector.
.TP
.B n
Next inspector page.
.TP
.B p
Previous inspector page.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/spacegl_hud
HUD executable.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spacegl_diag (1),
.BR spacegl_viewer (1),
.BR spacegl_server (1)
